  SUMMARY OF KEY FINDINGS
================================================================================

Dataset: 627,491 trials across 30 models and 32 conditions.

1. Mechanism decomposition: 9 baseline variants tested against
   main baseline (75.0% optimal). Significant deviations found for
   7 / 9 conditions (p < .05).

2. Position bias: Chose-optimal rates vary by chosen position
   (pos 0 = 3.0%, pos 4 = 81.0%, primacy = -78.0%).
   Chi-square p = 0.00e+00.

3. Category analysis: 20 categories, range = 57.5%.

4. Brand reasoning: Baseline chose_branded = 3.9%;
   brand_blind = 1.7% (Fisher p = 0.000000).

5. Vague paradox: See per-model tables above.

6. Cross-model consistency: 435 pairwise Spearman correlations.
   Mean rho = 0.609.

7. GEE stats: 34 unique assortments.
   ICC(model) = 0.0909, ICC(assortment) = 0.2903.

8. Provider comparison: chi2 = 331.0, p = 2.22e-70 (full dataset).

Done.
